pgTitle: Aeroflot accidents and incidents in the 1990s

rows.text: The aircraft, on loan from the Soviet Air Force, was operating a Kokand-Kabul cargo service. At m (ft), while on approach to Kabul, air traffic control ordered the pilot to discontinue the approach. The flaps and landing gear were retracted, yet the approach was continued. The aircraft stalled and crashed.
Control was lost and the aircraft crashed.
Crashed during climbout and was destroyed by fire. The aircraft had been stolen.
Forced landing, kilometres (mi) out of Guriev.
Destroyed by fire while undergoing repairs.
Crashed en route under unspecified circumstances.
Destroyed by fire while refuelling at Bratsk Airport.
Crashed kilometres (mi) away from the Kalga Airstrip.
Ended up upside down after crashing into snow.
Forced landed kilometres (mi) away from Uray.

The aircraft departed Kherpuchi and was due to operate a domestic scheduled passenger service, when it crashed into trees, kilometres (mi) out of the city, while attemtping to return to the aerodrome of departure, amid worsening weather conditions.
